  "format": "Sean and Amanda give their first, spoiler-free reactions to the two movies opening the same day, plus advice on running the double bill and box-office bets.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "Oppenheimer",
      "note": "spoiler-free first reactions",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Oppenheimer",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Christopher Nolan's adaptation of the Pulitzer-winning biography 'American Prometheus,' shot on 70mm IMAX with Cillian Murphy as J. Robert Oppenheimer. Sean calls it his favorite Nolan and the closest anyone has come to Oliver Stone's 'JFK,' citing the shifting stocks, aspect ratios, and cross-cutting. Amanda was mesmerized by the first two hours and openly bored by the procedural third; both flag Nolan's familiar problem writing the women. Cillian Murphy is their MVP."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "Barbie",
      "note": "spoiler-free first reactions",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Barbie",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Greta Gerwig's studio swing, written with Noah Baumbach, starring Margot Robbie and Ryan Gosling. Amanda loved it without distance and calls it an instant touchstone; Sean liked it but docked the Mattel-boardroom middle stretch, which makes the whole thing feel corporate. Both rate the first 40 minutes of Barbie Land as the standout and think Margot Robbie deserves an Oscar nomination."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
